This paper discusses the use of network coding in critical infrastructure networks, which are typically studied in the computer networks (cs.NI) and cybersecurity (cs.CR) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of programmable data-planes, which falls under the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of linear network coding, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and the optimization of network performance (cs.DC).
